      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TRUST ME (6) scored impressively two back then was always well back and could manage only a 5.5 lengths 7th at this track (28.21). Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from three attempts. Can bounce back. CANYA BYPASS (1) turned spotting a big start finishing sixth (28.28) last time in a Grade 5/6 at this track. Solid record here winning two races. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings four times from five starts. Should be about the mark. SUNSET PARIS (4) doesn't win out of turn. Finished in the minors latest when third (28.15) at this track and may be close to breaking through. Has a good record here including three wins. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Expected to feature again. IMPRESS SEMINYAK (2) is last start winner who looks one of the chances.",
